Privacy Policy

Last updated: [Wed 18 Sept 2024]

Jog Inventory Application ("Inventory") is developed for internal use to manage fabric and material inventory, track available materials, and facilitate the creation of material and forecast requests without coding. This privacy policy outlines how we handle personal and inventory-related data within the App.

1. Purpose of the App

The App is intended for internal use within Jog Digital Innovations to help manage fabric and material inventory, streamline material requests, and improve forecasting. It is not available to the general public, and access is restricted to authorized personnel only.

2. Information We Collect

Inventory Data: The App collects and stores information related to the available fabric and material inventory, including item types, quantities, and requests for materials.
User Data: For authorized users, we may collect user credentials such as usernames and work email addresses. This information is used solely to provide access to the App and its features.
3. How We Use the Information

Inventory Management: The App is designed to keep track of the available stock of materials and fabrics.
Request Processing: We use the data to process material and forecast requests, ensuring the necessary resources are available and properly allocated.
4. Data Security

We take appropriate security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. Access to the App is restricted to authorized personnel, and data is stored securely within [Your Companyâ€™s] internal systems.

5. Data Sharing

The data collected by the App is not shared with any third parties unless required by law or with express permission from Jog Digital InnovationsJog Digital Innovations. All data remains within the organization's internal systems.

6. User Rights

As an internal user, you have the right to access, update, or delete any personal information stored in the App, subject to approval by your administrator. If you have any concerns about your data, please contact [Contact Information].

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the App, and we encourage you to review the policy periodically.

